  "instructions": [
    "Marinate the beef fillet with salt, pepper, smoked paprika, and olive oil for 15 minutes.",
    "Preheat a skillet over medium-high heat and sear the steak 3-4 minutes per side, until desired doneness (internal temperature 57-60\u00b0C for medium-rare).",
    "Let the steak rest for 5 minutes, then slice thinly against the grain.",
    "Warm the flatbread in a dry skillet or oven for 1-2 minutes.",
    "Layer the sliced steak, onion, tomato, cucumber, and parsley onto the flatbread.",
    "Whisk yogurt, garlic, sumac, cumin, and salt together to make the sauce.",
    "Drizzle the yogurt sauce over the filling.",
    "Fold the flatbread into a wrap, sealing the edges, and serve immediately."
